===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Originally a {{liushu|p|nocap=y}} – an oven. {{zh-l|*虍}} and {{zh-l|*皿}} were added in the {{w|Chinese bronze inscriptions|bronze inscriptions}}, and the oven pictogram came to be written {{zh-l|*田}}, making the current form a {{Han compound|虍|田|皿|ls=psc|c1=p|c2=s|c3=s|t2=pictogram of an oven|t3=vessel|nocap=y}}. This sense (“oven”) is now represented by the character {{zh-l|爐}}.

===Etymology===
;black
:Inside Chinese, {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} minimally reconstructs {{och-l|盧|tr= {{IPAfont|*râ}}}}, which he relates {{och-l|驪|tr= {{IPAfont|*rê ~ re}}}} (minimally reconstructed in {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2009}}) by pointing out the vowel alternation {{IPAfont|*a}} vs. {{IPAfont|*e ~ i}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}});
:Outside Chinese, {{zh-ref|Coblin (1986)}} compares it to {{cog|bo|རོག་པོ||black animal; black, reddish, yellowish brown}} yet {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} notes that the rimes do not match.

